listings.description: Molly is sharing some of her all-time best dessert recipes...from cookies to squares and definitely donuts in between. Duh!

Ree Drummond is revealing her favourite shortcuts as she shares fast and festive last-minute ideas for the holidays.

In round one, chefs roll the dice to determine that their favorite dessert must include beef jerky.

In a world of convenience food, four scratch chefs show Guy Fieri what happens when convenience goes out the window. They have to make each component in their dishes entirely from scratch, like bread for their soup-and-sandwich combo.

A Texas couple moved to Las Vegas to be closer to family, but their outdated kitchen and dining room just won't work for their themed dinner parties. Drew and Jonathan step in to turn their house into an entertainer's dream with a dose of Vegas glam.

A skeleton is found on an abandoned plot of land, but before investigators can figure out who killed her, they have to figure out who she is.
A little boy is found alone and in a panic. When police go to his home, they find his grandparents dead in their bedroom.
The mother of a suspiciously murdered four-month-old was convicted, but an explanation for the death would come five months later from the most unlikely of sources: his newborn brother.

Laura Houghteling left her Bethesda home and walked to the station to take a train to work. A peculiar strand of hair found in Laura's hairbrush enabled investigators to unravel the mystery of her disappearance.
Fire sweeps through a mansion, killing two children, all evidence leads to the mother.
A man confesses to killing his wife, but forensic evidence may lead to another suspect.
Police exhume the body of a murdered woman to study bite wounds, which eventually lead to the killer.

Police believed that a husband murdered his wife after they learn that he had taken out a life insurance policy on her shortly before she died. When an investigator recreates the fall, the results are surprising.
In 2001, Andrea Yates drowned her five small children in the bathtub of their Houston home. Her bizarre explanation was that she did it to save her children from Satan.

In 1981, a gunman fires six shots at Ronald Reagan. What follows is a chaotic rush to save Reagan's life, confusion at the White House, and an urgent investigation to find out if this is a wider plot, or the work of a lone assassin.
In 2002, a sniper terrorizes Washington D.C. and the surrounding suburbs, randomly targeting ordinary citizens. Ten are killed, three wounded.
Writing style reveals Unabomber's identity when Ted Kaczynski's sister-in-law recognizes his phrasing in his manifesto.

In 2007, Amanda Knox, an American exchange student living in Italy, was arrested and tried for the murder of her roommate. The evidence was shockingly graphic, but the DNA was inconclusive. A look at the case and where things stand today.
Bite marks on a murder victims’ body twice lead to Ray Krone's conviction, but the DNA evidence tells another story.

In 1995, Hank Skinner was sentenced to death for a New Year's Eve triple-homicide of his family. Five years later, students from the Northwestern University start to examine the case and discover that key evidence was not examined for DNA.
Prosecutor used video testimony to link drunk driver to hit-and-run which killed a child.
When a gas station/ convenience store employee is found shot at point blank range, investigators find the entire murder has been caught on the store's videotape security camera.

17-year old Casey Crowder vanished early one Sunday morning after her car ran out of gas outside of Dumas, Arkansas. With no leads and no witnesses, investigators are desperate to find any CCTV cameras that can lead them to the missing teen.

On a freezing winter night, a hardworking mother doesn't make it home from work. As dawn breaks, her body is found in a churchyard. With the city in panic, Police turn to the city's surveillance cameras... hoping they can help catch a brutal murderer.

On September 7th, 2009, 27-year-old Jessika Kalaher is found strangled in her car in Cedar Park, Texas. With her wallet and car keys missing, detectives turn to security cameras to answer who and why.

On February 14th, 2014, pregnant college student Loretta Saunders vanishes without trace. Her trail runs cold after she is spotted on CCTV at her apartment building. The race is now on to find her before it's too late.

listings.episodeTitle: The Man in the Black Hat
listings.description: On April 14, 2009, 25-year old student Julissa Brisman is found shot and bound in an upmarket hotel room in Boston. With no witnesses to the crime, investigators turn to surveillance cameras in the surrounding area and quickly unravel a serial attacker.

Cynthia Langrall is shot dead while out for morning jog through the Hillcrest Ranch neighborhood in Glendale, Arizona. Detectives obtain home surveillance footage, which helps to identify the murderer's vehicle, but may not lead to the actual killer.

A night of celebration ends in horror when 29-year-old Adrianne Robert is found dead by her roommate. Police retrace Adrianne's footsteps and discover the club she visited is equipped with security cameras.
The body of a 20-year-old woman turns up in the most gruesome way imaginable severed and stuffed into trash bags.
When Dorian Bluford moves to a new city to be closer to a friend his family doesn't know, he's brutally murdered stabbed 37 times in the chest.

A US soldier who's been to war in two foreign lands meets harm in Upstate New York and his killers may have been his fellow GIs. Then, a young father and aspiring politician disappears, with the main clue his last, haunting voicemail.
When LeRyan Nicholson's sisters investigate his disappearance, they uncover a series of secrets that lead them to the heartbreaking truth.

A young woman living on an isolated pig farm in Kentucky seemingly vanishes without a trace just before Christmas. When the disturbing truth reveals itself, police find they have more questions than answers.
A young woman on a trip to her father's homeland goes missing, then turns up brutally murdered. Another young mother and her baby are shot as they drive along a highway.

In March 2014, the bodies of two women lie behind a grocery store in Galveston, Texas. With few clues to go on, the homicide investigation gets off to a slow start. A trail of surveillance footage could possibly reveal who killed the women and why.
